  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/sending-closure-risks-data-race"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Sending closure risks causing data races (SendingClosureRisksDataRace)"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Sharing mutable state between concurrent tasks can cause data races in your program. Resolve this error by only accessing mutable state in one task at a time.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If a type does not conform to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Sendable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", the compiler enforces that each instance of that type is only accessed by one concurrency domain at a time. The compiler also prevents you from capturing values in closures that are sent to another concurrency domain if the value can be accessed from the original concurrency domain too.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "class MyModel {",
            "  var count: Int = 0",
            "",
            "  func perform() {",
            "    Task {",
            "      self.update()",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "",
            "  func update() { count += 1 }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The compiler diagnoses the capture of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "self",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the task closure:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "| class MyModel {",
            "|   func perform() {",
            "|     Task {",
            "|     `- error: passing closure as a 'sending' parameter risks causing data races between code in the current isolation context and concurrent execution of the closure",
            "|       self.update()",
            "|            `- note: closure captures 'self' which is accessible to code in the current isolation context",
            "|     }",
            "|   }"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This code is invalid because the task that calls ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "perform()",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " runs concurrently with the task that calls ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "update()",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type does not conform to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Sendable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and it has unprotected mutable state that both concurrent tasks could access simultaneously.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To eliminate the risk of data races, all tasks that can access the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instance must be serialized. The easiest way to accomplish this is to isolate ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to a global actor, such as the main actor:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "@MainActor",
            "class MyModel {",
            "  func perform() {",
            "    Task {",
            "      self.update()",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "",
            "  func update() { ... }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This resolves the data race because the two tasks that can access the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " value must switch to the main actor to access its state and methods.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The other approach to resolving the error is to ensure that only one task has access to the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " value at a time. For example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "class MyModel {",
            "  static func perform(model: sending MyModel) {",
            "    Task {",
            "      model.update()",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "",
            "  func update() { ... }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This code is safe from data races because the caller of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "perform",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " cannot access the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "model",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameter again after the call. The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "sending",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameter modifier indicates that the implementation of the function sends the value to a different concurrency domain, so it’s no longer safe to access the value in the caller. This ensures that only one task has access to the value at a time.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
